      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If your tremors are severe enough that you can barely hold a spoon, that is a clear sign that your dosage or levels need immediate professional adjustment. Do not wait a few days when your motor control is compromised; that is not a minor side effect. You need to call your prescribing physician *today* to discuss a potential dose modification, and if they are unavailable, you should seek urgent care.",
      "source": "target",
